markdown <<MARKDOWN
How many binary place values are required for the sum of decimal numbers 2 and 6?
MARKDOWN
teacher_markdown <<MARKDOWN
Learning Objective: **2.1.2** and Essential Knowledge statements: **2.1.2B**
<hr>
 (A) This is incorrect because you can only represent up to the decimal number 3 with 2 binary digits.

<hr>
 (B) This is incorrect because you can only represent up to the decimal number 7 with 3 binary digits.

<hr>
 (C) This is correct because the number 8 in decimal is represented by 1000 in binary.

<hr>
 (D) This is incorrect because it is unnecessary to use 5 bits when you can use 4.

MARKDOWN

